				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					<!--cached-Tue, 22 Jul 2014 03:18:29 +0000-->Annette,<br />
<br />
You more than likely received the error message when trying to edit the configure.php because you had the file permissions set correctly &#33;  Yes, correctly.  The TWO configure.php files should have permissions of 444, which will not allow you to over write them.  So, when you edited the file and tried to upload it back to the server, you received the error.  In future, rename the old configure.php to configure1.php (or something similar) and then upload the edited file to the server.<br />
<br />
ALWAYS remember to change the file permissions back to 444 for the two configure.php files.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Chris
					
					<br />
					
				</div>
				
				
